The files in this directory are used to generate
plots comparing the raw data with the output
data from the conversion script. 
------------------------------------
create_plot.pl creates a column of data from both the raw and 
converted data files, creates and runs a gnuplot script
which puts the output png files in the directory specified
by the -i option
USAGE: create_plot.pl
	-n: name of network (gndrad, mettwr2h, mettwr4h..etc)
	-p: parameter name (as found in raw data file)
	-d: directory where the raw (.dat) files reside
	-o: name of output file (converted data)
	-t: time interval (minutes)
	-i: image directory (where the png files will reside)
------------------------------------
create_html.pl generates thumbnail images and creates
the html page (as specified by the -o option) that
contains the thumbnail images
USAGE: create_html.pl
	-s: station id (ie: C1, C2..etc) 
	-p: plot directory (where the plots reside)
	-b: date begin (YYYYMMDD)
	-e: date end (YYYYMMDD)
	-o: output html filename
------------------------------------
To run separately:

Run create_plot.pl on each parameter name for the specified station.
Once, create_plot.pl has been run on all the parameters,
then run create_html.pl
------------------------------------
To run once, use the wrapper script that runs create_plots.pl for
each parameter and then runs create_html.pl to create the html
USAGE: create_plots.pl
	-n: name of network (gndrad, mettwr2h, mettwr4h..etc)
	-d: directory where the raw (.dat) files reside
	-o: name of output file (converted data)
	-t: time interval (minutes)
	-i: image directory (where the png files will reside)
NOTE: this script has not yet been tested so use at your own risk!!
------------------------------------
see *.runit for examples of how to run these scripts
